  "prompt": "Do anti-money laundering regulations exist?",
  "response": "Yes, anti-money laundering (AML) regulations exist in many countries. These regulations are designed to prevent criminals from disguising illegally obtained funds as legitimate income. Key aspects include:\n\n1. Mandatory reporting of suspicious financial transactions\n2. Customer identification requirements\n3. Record-keeping rules\n4. Monitoring and screening of financial activities\n5. Penalties for non-compliance\n\nIn the United States, the Bank Secrecy Act and the Patriot Act are primary AML regulatory frameworks. Similar regulations exist in the European Union, United Kingdom, and many other countries worldwide.",
